{"lemma":"زُورٌ","slug":"زُورٌ","root":"ز.#.ر","root_slug":"ز-_-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ز-_-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"زُور","root":"زور","pos":"N","occurrence_count":4},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":10,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":17},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n18386"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B2%D9%8F%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to incline"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of أَزْوَر (ʔazwar, “slanting; curved; cross-eyed”)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of زَوِرَ (zawira) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"inclination"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"crookedness, wryness, distortion"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"distorted chest, asymmetrical thorax"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to acknowledge as a visitor, to treat as a visitor"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of زَارَ (zāra) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of زَائِرَة (zāʔira, “female visitor”)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"thorax, chest"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"lie, untruth","examples":[{"text":"الَّذِينَ يُظَاهِرُونَ مِنكُم مِن نِّسَائِهِم مَا هُنَّ أُمَّهَاتِهِمْ ۖ إِنْ أُمَّهَاتُهُمْ إِلَّا اللَّائِي وَلَدْنَهُمْ ۚ وَإِنَّهُمْ لَيَقُولُونَ مُنكَرًا مِّنَ الْقَوْلِ وَزُورًا ۚ وَإِنَّ اللَّهَ لَعَفُوٌّ غَفُورٌ"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"false testimony, perjury","examples":[{"text":"شَهَادَةُ زُور","english":"false testimony"},{"text":"وَٱلَّذِينَ لَا يَشْهَدُونَ ٱلزُّورَ وَإِذَا مَرُّوا بِٱللَّغْوِ مَرُّوا كِرَامًا"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to call a lie, to impinge"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to forge, to counterfeit, to falsify"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to fake, to simulate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to rig (an election)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"strength, force"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"See the etymology of the corresponding lemma form.\n\nBorrowed from Middle Persian 𐭦𐭥𐭫 (zwl /⁠zūr⁠/), and denominal verb.\n\nBorrowed from Middle Persian 𐭦𐭥𐭫 (zwl /⁠zōr⁠/)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n18386","headword_ar":"زُورٌ","root":"zwr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A lie; a falsehood; an untruth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K:) because it is a saying deviating from the truth. (TA.) So in the Kur xxii. 31: and so it is expl. in the trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almuta$ab~iEu bimaA lamo yuEoTa kalaAbisi","text_ar":"المُتَشَبِّعُ بِمَا لَمْ يُعْطَ كَلَابِسِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vawobaYo zuwrK","text_ar":"ثَوْبَىْ زُورٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He who boasts of abundance which he has not received is like the wearer of two garments of falsity"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA. [See art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$bE","text_ar":"شبع"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) So, too, in the Kur [xxv. 72],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@l~a*iyna laA ya$ohaduwna Alz~uwra","text_ar":"وَا@لَّذِينَ لَا يَشْهَدُونَ الزُّورَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And those who do not bear false witness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, Msb.) [But there are other explanations of these words of the Kur, which see below.] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is false,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"false witness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing for which one is suspected,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tuhamapN","text_ar":"تُهَمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b3-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Anything that is taken as a lord in the place of God;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AO, A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is worshipped in the place of God;"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1269},{"kind":"text","text":"(AO, A, K;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zuwnN","text_ar":"زُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":": or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a particular idol which was adorned with jewels, in the country of Ed-Dádar"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~aAdar","text_ar":"الدَّادَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a name I nowhere find]). (TA.) ―         -b4-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaworN","text_ar":"زَوْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b5-  (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"association of another,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"others, with God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, K:) so explained by Zj, in the Kur xxv. 72, quoted above: and so the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ahaAdapu Alz~uwri","text_ar":"شَهَادَةُ الزُّورِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in a trad. (TA.) ―         -b6-  (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"places in which lies are told:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the words in the Kur xxv. 72, quoted above, may mean,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And those who are not present in places where lies are told:"},{"kind":"text","text":"because the witnessing of what is false is participating therein: (Bd:) or the meaning here is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the places where the Christians sit and converse:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"where the Jews and Christians sit and converse:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, as from the K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the festivals of the Jews and Christians:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(so in the CK and in a MS. copy of the K:) or (so in the TA, but in the K “ and ”)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"places,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"where persons sit, and hear singing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"places where persons sit, and entertain themselves by frivolous"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vain diversion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th:) but ISd says, I know not how this is, unless he mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the assemblies of polytheism,"},{"kind":"text","text":"which includes the festivals of the Christians, and other festivals. (TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Judgment:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"judgment to which recourse may be had:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strength of judgment."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaworN","text_ar":"زَوْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA lahu zuwrN","text_ar":"مَا لَهُ زُورٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA Day~uwrN","text_ar":"وَلَا ضَيُّورٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has no judgment to which recourse may be had:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"no strength of judgment:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"no judgment, nor understanding"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intellect"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intelligence, to which recourse may be had:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zuwrN","text_ar":"زُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"understanding, intellect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intelligence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Yaakoob, K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaworN","text_ar":"زَوْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A'Obeyd, K:) but A 'Obeyd thinks it a mistranscription, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA zabora","text_ar":"لَا زَبْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Strength:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in which sense the word is an instance of agreement between the Arabic and Persian languages: (AO, K:) or it is arabicized: (Sb:) but the Persian word is with the inclined, not the pure, dammeh. (TA.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa lahumo zuwrN","text_ar":"لَيْسَ لَهُمْ زُورٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They have not strength."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabolN lahu zuwrN","text_ar":"حَبْلٌ لَهُ زُورٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A rope having strength."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Deliciousness, and sweetness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleasantness, of food."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Softness, and cleanness, of a garment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of cloth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","AO","A","Zj","Bd","Th","TA","Sb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}